import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Life Expectancy', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='fertility', y='life_expect', hue='cluster', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Cluster', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
